Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or
use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the tomatoes and garlic onto a piece of #foil{} with the @butter{10%g},
then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to
create a parcel.

When the oven is hot, roast on the bottom shelf until softened,
~{20-25%minutes}.

Trim and quarter the @courgette{2} lengthways.

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the
@flaked almonds{15%g} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted,
~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once toasted, transfer to a small #bowl{} and pop the pan on high heat (no oil).

Add the courgette and cook on both cut sides until charred, ~{3-4%minutes}
each side. Turn only every couple of mins - this will result in the courgette
picking up some char marks.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into
thin strips.

Transfer the charred courgettes to another #baking tray{} and pop the peppers
alongside.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Drizzle the veg with some @oil{} and sprinkle over the
@roasted spice and herb blend{1}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss
to coat.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until softened, ~{12-14%minutes}.

== Zhoug Couscous ==

While everything's in the oven, put the @couscous{120%g} in a bowl.

Pour in the @boiled water{240%ml} for the couscous, stir in the
@vegetable stock paste{10%g}, then cover tightly with #cling film{}.

Leave to the side for ~{10%minutes} or until almost ready to serve.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1} (stalks and all).

== Tomato Yoghurt Sauce ==

Once the tomatoes have roasted, open the foil to let the steam out and set
aside for a few mins.

When the couscous is ready, fluff it up with a #fork{}.

Stir through the @zhoug style paste{50%g}, roasted peppers and three quarters of
the parsley.

Just before serving, transfer the garlic and roasted tomatoes to another bowl.
Squish the tomatoes and stir through the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g},
then season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Share the couscous into your bowls and top with the charred courgettes, then
drizzle over the tomato yoghurt sauce.

Scatter with the flaked almonds and remaining parsley to finish. Enjoy!